&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Systems Engineer will join EG&#39;s Systems Infrastructure team, which&amp;nbsp;is responsible for&amp;nbsp;all layers of technology in our environment, from networking to servers and application services, and will report to the&amp;nbsp;London&amp;nbsp;Head of Infrastructure. The firm&#39;s infrastructure is built using modern technologies, with a focus on creating robust, reusable components and the strategic use of automation. As a &quot;flat&quot; team, all members have exposure to, and&amp;nbsp;are responsible for, the design, implementation, operation, and support of our environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;The Systems Engineer will initially focus on day-to-day system administration and supporting end-user systems, with the opportunity to grow into other areas of our systems infrastructure over time,&amp;nbsp;ultimately managing&amp;nbsp;large projects independently. The ideal candidate will&amp;nbsp;demonstrate&amp;nbsp;technical aptitude in areas&amp;nbsp;they&#39;ve&amp;nbsp;worked in previously, along with the ability to think systemically and reason through problems they&amp;nbsp;haven&#39;t&amp;nbsp;yet&amp;nbsp;encountered. While new team members will receive support and mentorship from the rest of the team, they will also be expected to conduct independent research and propose both solutions to emerging problems and improvements to current processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
